 <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 2:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /sexx0r kalvorie</span><hr size=1> I think the design on this mod is great and the idea of taking a whole new fresh look at the ui is one we should do.<br>
<br>
I do have to say that spending over 50% of the screen on user interface is probably a bit too much for me.  While some powergamers might love having all their statistics and items availalble all the time, it does diminish the beauty of the rest of the game and cut down a lot on the information you get from the world around you.<br>
<br>
My philosophy has been to look at every visual element and determine if it is something I need to see all the time or not.  If not, I remove it or put it on a window I don't have up (like inventory).  Things like chat, health, mana, etc are things I want all the time.  Things like saves, ac, etc are things I might not need.<br>
<br>
Still, this ui has got me thinking a lot about what we can do and should do to make the UI better.<br>
<br>
