<br>
I am also going to experiment with viewport's, the layout of this UI seems very /viewport friendly. Does anyone else run in 1024x768 mode with this skin? And use /viewport? If so, what viewport setting did you use and how well did it work? I only have a 17&quot; monitor so I'm not certain if I can get away with cranking the resolution about 1024x768 as that may tun it all unreadable by me...<br>
<br>
Also, here are a couple of ideas I had that I think would go along well with this skin. I may try to hack them or someone who actually has XML skills and is more familiar than I with this stuff could try it and see how it works out.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> change the layout of the buff window</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I like the fact that this buff window uses the compact buff icons and shows the effect name with the effect name background set differently for beneficial vs detrimental effects. But, I think the layout could be tweaked to make it less jarring to the eye.<br>
<br>
Here's how it is now:<br>
&lt;left window border&gt;&lt;icon #n&gt; &lt;effect name #n, left justified text&gt;&lt;right window border&gt;<br>
<br>
Here's what I think would look better:<br>
&lt;left window border&gt;&lt;effect name #n, right justified text&gt;&lt;icon #n&gt;&lt;right window border&gt;<br>
<br>
As a more concrete example, lets say I had Familiar, Shield of the Magi, See Invisible, Barrier of Force, and Aegolism up. I also just left HoT and a ton of buffs have faded <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Under the existing buff screen I would have a layout like so (assuming I set the right border of the buff window along the right border of the screen):<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
